{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"toefl-sentences","unitId":"sentence-026","title":"Sentence 26","sectionId":"sentences-021","sectionTitle":"Sentence 21-30","pageStart":182,"pageEnd":187,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":37,"duplicateEntryCount":6,"pages":[{"number":182,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Sentence 26"},{"type":"text","text":"By fossils, we mean traces of prehistoric animals such as bones,"},{"type":"text","text":"which become mineralized, or impressions of bones or organs that are left"},{"type":"text","text":"in stone."},{"type":"text","text":"提到化石，我们指的是史前生物的遗迹，比如已经矿化的骨"},{"type":"text","text":"头，或者是骨头或器官在石头上留下的印记。"},{"type":"section","text":"语法笔记"},{"type":"text","text":"本句主干是“By fossils, we mean traces of prehistoric animals”。句中"},{"type":"text","text":"such as后是由or连接的两个并列成分，即bones和impressions of bones or"},{"type":"text","text":"organs，这两个并列成分后面分别带有一个定语从句。其中bones后是"},{"type":"text","text":"which引导的非限制性定语从句，impressions of bones or organs后是that"},{"type":"text","text":"引导的定语从句。"},{"type":"section","text":"核心词表"},{"type":"entry","text":"fossil /ˈfɑːsl/ n. 化石","headword":"fossil"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 fossil fuel化石燃料"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 fossilize vt. 使成化石"},{"type":"text","text":"fossilized a. 成化石的"},{"type":"entry","text":"trace /treɪs/ n. 痕迹；遗迹","headword":"trace"},{"type":"note","text":"同义 imprint n. 痕迹"}]},{"number":183,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"mineralize /ˈmɪnərəˌlaɪz/ vt. 使矿物化","headword":"mineralize"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 mineral n. 矿物"},{"type":"text","text":"mineralization n. 矿化"},{"type":"entry","text":"impression /ɪmˈpreʃn/ n. 印记，压痕；印象","headword":"impression"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 impress vt. 使铭记"},{"type":"entry","text":"organ /ˈɔːrɡən/ n. 器官","headword":"organ"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 organ transplant 器官移植"},{"type":"section","text":"主题归纳"},{"type":"text","text":"与“化石”相关的词："},{"type":"entry","text":"antiquity /ænˈtɪkwəti/ n. 古迹；古物","headword":"antiquity"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 antique a. 古老的"},{"type":"entry","text":"biochemical /ˌbaɪoʊˈkemɪkl/ a. 生物化学的","headword":"biochemical"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 biochemical weapon 生化武器"},{"type":"text","text":"body fossil 实体化石"},{"type":"entry","text":"carbonization /ˌkɑːrbənəˈzeɪʃn/ n. 碳化；碳化物","headword":"carbonization"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 carbon n. 碳"},{"type":"text","text":"chemical reduction 化学还原"}]},{"number":184,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"diagenesis /ˌdaɪəˈdʒɛnɪsɪs/ n. 岩化作用","headword":"diagenesis"},{"type":"text","text":"dinosaur fossil 恐龙化石"},{"type":"entry","text":"formation /fɔːrˈmeɪʃn/ n. 形成，构成","headword":"formation"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 form（形成）+ation→形成"},{"type":"text","text":"fossil record 化石记录"},{"type":"entry","text":"fossiliferous /ˌfɒsɪˈlɪfərəs/ a. 含有化石的","headword":"fossiliferous"},{"type":"entry","text":"fossilization /ˌfɑːsələˈzeɪʃn/ n. 石化","headword":"fossilization"},{"type":"note","text":"同义 petrifaction n. 石化"},{"type":"entry","text":"geological /ˌdʒiːəˈlɑːdʒɪkl/ a. 地质的，地质学的","headword":"geological"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 geological time 地质时间"},{"type":"text","text":"index fossil 标准化石"}]},{"number":185,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"microfossil /ˈmaɪkrəʊˌfɒsəl/ n. 微化石","headword":"microfossil"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 micro（微小）+fossil（化石）→微化石"},{"type":"entry","text":"paleontology /ˌpeɪliənˈtɑlədʒi/ n. 古生物学","headword":"paleontology"},{"type":"entry","text":"precipitation /prɪˌsɪpɪˈteɪʃn/ n. 沉淀","headword":"precipitation"},{"type":"note","text":"同义 sediment n. 沉淀"},{"type":"entry","text":"remains /rɪˈmeɪnz/ n. 古代遗物，遗迹","headword":"remains"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 preserved remains 保存下来的遗骸"},{"type":"text","text":"rock formation 岩层"},{"type":"text","text":"sedimentary layer 沉淀岩层"},{"type":"entry","text":"skeletal /ˈskelətl/ a. 骨骼的，骸骨的","headword":"skeletal"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 skeleton n. 骨骼"},{"type":"entry","text":"specimen /ˈspesɪmən/ n. 标本","headword":"specimen"},{"type":"note","text":"同义 sample n. 标本"},{"type":"entry","text":"subfossil /ˈs